## Role of Nurses in Promoting Collaboration

Nurses are central to care transitions, acting as:

- **Patient Advocates**: Representing patient preferences and concerns.
- **Information Hubs**: Providing accurate patient data to the team.
- **Transition Coordinators**: Managing logistics and ensuring follow-up.

Nurses facilitate collaboration by conducting thorough assessments, managing transfer processes, and enhancing communication among team members and with patients ([Wolters Kluwer Health, 2019](https://www.wolterskluwer.com/en/solutions/ovid/best-practices-for-safe-and-successful-care-transitions)).

