## Use of Evidence-Based Toolkits and Resources

Facilities leverage evidence-based toolkits to standardize and improve transition processes:

| Toolkit/Resource                                    | Description                                                                                       | Care Settings Covered                                   |
|----------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| **ASPIRE Guide and Toolkit (AHRQ)**                 | Framework to reduce Medicaid readmissions through data analysis and cross-continuum collaboration.| Inpatient, Outpatient, SNF, Home Care                   |
| **Care Transitions Program Toolkit (Eric Coleman)** | Tools for patients and families to navigate hospital discharge and improve handoffs.             | Inpatient, Outpatient, SNF, Home Care                   |
| **IDEAL Discharge Planning (AHRQ)**                 | Discharge planning strategy emphasizing patient and family engagement and teach-back methods.    | Inpatient, Outpatient, SNF, Home Care                   |
| **MARQUIS Medication Reconciliation Manual**        | Best practices for medication reconciliation to reduce errors during transitions.                | All care settings                                       |
| **TST – Targeted Solutions Tool (Joint Commission)**| Online tool measuring handoff effectiveness and providing solutions to improve transitions.      | All care settings                                       |

Implementing these toolkits fosters standardized workflows, enhances team communication, and engages patients and families actively in transitions ([Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, 2017](https://www.ahrq.gov/hai/tools/ambulatory-care/safe-transitions.html)).

